article.headline: Binghamton 67, New Hampshire 58
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Lazar Trifunovic's 19 points led four Binghampton players in double digits as the Bearcats defeated New Hampshire 67-58 on Thursday night. Mike Gordon added 13 for Binghamton, and Richard Forbes and Dwayne Jackson added 10 each. Binghamton (9-10, 5-2 America East) trailed New Hampshire (5-13, 2-4) 27-24 at the half, but pulled ahead in the second period, leading by 62-55 with 2:25 left in the game. Eric Gilchrese scored a 3-pointer for the Wildcats to cut the lead to 62-58, but Binghamton scored the last five points. Rony Tchatchoua, back in action after a six-game absence, scored a career-high 17 points for the Wildcats.
